A vintage-style funeral scene in a misty cemetery at dusk, featuring an ornate Victorian tombstone with a cracked, weathered blue "e" logo carved into the stone, surrounded by wilting flowers and autumn leaves scattered on the ground. Mourners in 1940s attire stand at a respectful distance, some holding black umbrellas despite no rain. A single crow perches atop the gravestone. The color palette emphasizes sepia tones with pops of faded blue from the logo, dramatic cloudy sky with rays of golden sunset breaking through. The mood is both solemn and slightly sardonic, suggesting relief mixed with ceremony.
